    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "Is MRI Face painful?",
        "answer": "No. It’s painless; you only hear loud knocking sounds.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "How long does the scan take?",
        "answer": "15–25 minutes for non-contrast; add 10 min if contrast is used.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I eat before MRI Face?",
        "answer": "Yes, unless contrast is planned—then fast 4 hours.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "When will I get my report?",
        "answer": "Same day at Cadabams Diagnostics; emailed within 6 hours.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Is contrast dye safe?",
        "answer": "Yes. Gadolinium is FDA-approved; allergy risk is extremely low.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What are the next steps after an MRI Face scan?",
        "answer": "Your referring doctor will review the **MRI FACE** scan report from our radiologist and discuss the findings with you. Depending on the results, the next steps could include a diagnosis, recommendations for further tests if needed, or the development of a treatment plan. If the scan was for a pediatric patient, these results may also help guide **pediatric therapy** referrals if appropriate."
      }
    ],
